Country-road path and speed controller.

This extends the steering-only controller with a simple longitudinal speed loop.
The controller measures speed projected onto the road reference-line tangent and
outputs front-axle drive torque plus per-wheel brake torque. Positive drive torque
is split across the two front wheels by the plant; brake torque is applied to all
four wheels opposing each wheel's spin direction.

